HEADWORD: Looper
<hw>Loop"er</hw> <pr>(l⟦oomac⟧p"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>An instrument, as a bodkin, for forming a loop in yarn, a cord,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The larva of any species of
geometrid moths. See <er>Geometrid</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loophole</ent>⟦br⟧
